#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="pi-tv-bu-vb-pc40"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:0.3"
msgid "Pācittiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on confession (_pācittiya_)"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:0.4"
msgid "Bhojanavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 40"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:0.5"
msgid "40. Dantaponasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on tooth-cleaners"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:1.0b"
msgid ""
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-cs-bu-pc40.1, pts-vp-en.2.344, ms2V_848
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Vesālī in the hall with the peaked "
"roof in the Great Wood."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu sabbapaṃsukūliko susāne viharati."
msgstr ""
"At that time a monk who only used discarded things was staying in a charnel "
"ground."

#. VAR: paribhuñjati → bhuñjati (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:1.3"
msgid ""
"So manussehi diyyamānaṃ na icchati paṭiggahetuṃ, susānepi rukkhamūlepi "
"ummārepi ayyavosāṭitakāni sāmaṃ gahetvā paribhuñjati."
msgstr ""
"He disliked receiving what was given by people. Instead he would take "
"whatever was offered to the dead at charnel grounds, at the foot of trees, "
"or at thresholds, and he would use that."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:1.4"
msgid "Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "People complained and criticized him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:1.5"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma ayaṃ bhikkhu amhākaṃ ayyavosāṭitakāni sāmaṃ gahetvā "
"paribhuñjissati."
msgstr "“How can this monk take the offerings to our ancestors and use them?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:1.6"
msgid ""
"Theroyaṃ bhikkhu vaṭharo manussamaṃsaṃ maññe khādatī”ti. One might even "
"suspect him of eating human flesh!”"
msgstr "This monk is big and strong."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, ms2V_849
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:1.7"
msgid ""
"Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those people,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:1.8"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:1.9"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:1.10"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma bhikkhu adinnaṃ mukhadvāraṃ āhāraṃ āharissatī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "“How can this monk eat food that has not been given?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:1.11"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, bhikkhu, adinnaṃ mukhadvāraṃ āhāraṃ āharasī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monk, that you do this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:1.12"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:1.13"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:1.14"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, adinnaṃ mukhadvāraṃ āhāraṃ āharissasi."
msgstr "Foolish man, how can you eat food that has not been given?"

#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.345
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:1.15"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:1.16"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:1.16a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Preliminary ruling"

#. HTML: </h3><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc3, pts-vp-pli4.90, ms2V_850
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:1.17"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu adinnaṃ mukhadvāraṃ āhāraṃ āhareyya, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk eats food that has not been given, he commits an offense "
"entailing confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p class="endsection">
#. REF: sc4, ms2V_851
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:1.18"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. VAR: udakadantapone → udakadantapoṇe (s1-3, pts1, mr)
#. REF: sc5, pts-cs-bu-pc40.2, ms2V_852
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū udakadantapone kukkuccāyanti."
msgstr ""
"Soon afterwards the monks did not use water or tooth-cleaners because they "
"were afraid of wrongdoing."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:2.2"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "They told the Master …"

#. HTML: <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:2.3"
msgid "“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, udakadantaponaṃ sāmaṃ gahetvā paribhuñjituṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Monks, I allow you to use water and tooth-cleaners after taking them "
"yourselves."

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:2.4"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:2.4a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule">
#. VAR: udakadantaponā → ... poṇā (s1-3, pts1)
#. REF: sc6, ms2V_853
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:2.5"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu adinnaṃ mukhadvāraṃ āhāraṃ āhareyya, aññatra "
"udakadantaponā, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk eats food that has not been given, except for water and tooth-"
"cleaners, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:3.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc7, pts-cs-bu-pc40.3.1, ms2V_854
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:3.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:3.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. HTML: </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:3.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:3.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr ""
"… he monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through "
"a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is "
"unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:3.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc8, ms2V_855
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:3.1.6"
msgid "Adinnaṃ nāma"
msgstr "That has not been given:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:3.1.7"
msgid "appaṭiggahitakaṃ vuccati."
msgstr "what has not been received is what is meant."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc9, ms2V_856
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:3.1.8"
msgid "Dinnaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Given:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:3.1.9"
msgid ""
"kāyena vā kāyapaṭibaddhena vā nissaggiyena vā dente hatthapāse ṭhito kāyena "
"vā kāyapaṭibaddhena vā paṭiggaṇhāti, etaṃ dinnaṃ nāma."
msgstr ""
"standing within arm’s reach of one giving by body or by what is connected to "
"his body or by releasing, he receives it by body or by what is connected to "
"his body—this is called “given.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc10, ms2V_857
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:3.1.10"
msgid "Āhāro nāma"
msgstr "Food:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:3.1.11"
msgid "udakadantaponaṃ ṭhapetvā yaṃ kiñci ajjhoharaṇīyaṃ, eso āhāro nāma."
msgstr ""
"whatever is edible, apart from water and tooth-cleaners—this is called "
"“food.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc11, ms2V_858
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:3.1.12"
msgid "Aññatra udakadantaponāti"
msgstr "Except for water and tooth-cleaners:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:3.1.13"
msgid "ṭhapetvā udakadantaponaṃ."
msgstr "apart from water and tooth-cleaners."

#. HTML: </span></p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc12, ms2V_859, pts-vp-en.2.346
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:3.1.14"
msgid "“Khādissāmi bhuñjissāmī”ti gaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he takes it with the intention of eating it, he commits an offense of "
"wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:3.1.15"
msgid "Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "For every mouthful, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:3.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc13, pts-cs-bu-pc40.3.2, ms2V_860
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:3.2.1"
msgid ""
"Appaṭiggahitake appaṭiggahitakasaññī adinnaṃ mukhadvāraṃ āhāraṃ āhāreti, "
"aññatra udakadantaponā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it has not been received, and he does not perceive it as received, and he "
"eats it, except for water and tooth-cleaners, he commits an offense "
"entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:3.2.2"
msgid ""
"Appaṭiggahitake vematiko adinnaṃ mukhadvāraṃ āhāraṃ āhāreti, aññatra "
"udakadantaponā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it has not been received, but he is unsure of it, and he eats it, except "
"for water and tooth-cleaners, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:3.2.3"
msgid ""
"Appaṭiggahitake paṭiggahitakasaññī adinnaṃ mukhadvāraṃ āhāraṃ āhāreti, "
"aññatra udakadantaponā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it has not been not received, but he perceives it as received, and he "
"eats it, except for water and tooth-cleaners, he commits an offense "
"entailing confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14, ms2V_861
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:3.2.4"
msgid "Paṭiggahitake appaṭiggahitakasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it has been received, but he does not perceive it as received, he commits "
"an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:3.2.5"
msgid "Paṭiggahitake vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it has been received, but he is unsure if it has, he commits an offense "
"of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:3.2.6"
msgid "Paṭiggahitake paṭiggahitakasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr ""
"If it has been received, and he perceives it as received, there is no "
"offense."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:3.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc15, pts-cs-bu-pc40.3.3, ms2V_862
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:3.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:3.3.2"
msgid "udakadantapone,"
msgstr "if it is water or tooth-cleaners;"

# NOTE: These are dung, urine, ash, and clay, see [](MS.3.1233).
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:3.3.3"
msgid ""
"cattāri mahāvikaṭāni sati paccaye asati kappiyakārake sāmaṃ gahetvā "
"paribhuñjati,"
msgstr ""
"if, when there is a reason, but there is no attendant, he himself takes the "
"four filthy edibles and eats them;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:3.3.4"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:3.3.5"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc16, ms2V_863
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:3.3.6"
msgid "Dantaponasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dasamaṃ."
msgstr "The tenth rule, the training rule on tooth-cleaners, is finished."

#. HTML: </p><p class="endchapter"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:3.3.7"
msgid "Bhojanavaggo catuttho."
msgstr "The fourth chapter on food is finished."

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection summary">
#. REF: sc17, ms2V_864
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:3.3.8"
msgid "Tassuddānaṃ"
msgstr "This is the summary:"

#. HTML: </p><div class="uddana"><p>
#. REF: sc18, ms2V_865
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:3.3.9"
msgid "Piṇḍo gaṇaṃ paraṃ pūvaṃ,"
msgstr "Alms, group, another, biscuit,"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:3.3.10"
msgid "dve ca vuttā pavāraṇā;"
msgstr "And two on expressed satisfaction;"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:3.3.11"
msgid "Vikāle sannidhī khīraṃ,"
msgstr "At the wrong time, store, milk,"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc40:3.3.12"
msgid "dantaponena te dasāti."
msgstr "And with tooth-cleaner: those are the ten."
